# ğŸŒ± TipMeOverWaterer

**TipMeOverWaterer** is an ESP32-based automated plant watering system that periodically checks soil moisture levels and waters the plant as needed. It features an LCD interface, motor-controlled pump, and Telegram integration for remote status alerts.

---

## ğŸ“¦ Features

- ğŸŒ¿ Automatically waters the plant every 6 hours (or sooner if needed)
- ğŸ’§ Reads real-time soil moisture data via an analog sensor
- ğŸ“² Sends Telegram alerts when watering is triggered or the water tank is empty
- ğŸ“Ÿ Button-activated LCD displays current soil moisture level
- âš™ï¸ Uses FreeRTOS tasks for modular and responsive operation
- ğŸ”‹ Designed with power efficiency and sleep modes in mind (expandable)

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Hardware Requirements

- ESP32 Dev Board  
- Soil Moisture Sensor (Analog)  
- Motor or Pump (controlled via GPIOs)  
- Relay or Motor Driver (e.g., L298N)  
- I2C LCD (16x2)  
- Push Button  
- Internet access via WiFi

---

## ğŸ”Œ Pin Configuration

| Component            | ESP32 Pin |
|---------------------|-----------|
| Soil Moisture Sensor| GPIO35    |
| LCD SDA             | GPIO21    |
| LCD SCL             | GPIO22    |
| LCD Button          | GPIO25    |
| Motor IN1 (MOTOR1A) | GPIO27    |
| Motor IN2 (MOTOR2A) | GPIO26    |

